### AutoTallerManager endpoint smoke tests
### Cambia baseUrl y pega tokens reales despues de hacer login.
### En VS Code instala "REST Client" o usa JetBrains HTTP Client.

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@json = application/json

@adminToken = paste-admin-jwt-here
@receptionistToken = paste-receptionist-jwt-here
@mechanicToken = paste-mechanic-jwt-here
@clientToken = paste-client-jwt-here

@id = 1
@personId = 1
@userId = 1
@roleId = 1
@vehicleId = 1
@serviceOrderId = 1
@orderServiceId = 1
@partId = 1
@invoiceId = 1
@unique = {{$timestamp}}

### AUTH - registrar cliente
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register-client
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "documentTypeId": 1,
  "documentNumber": "TEST-CLIENT-{{unique}}",
  "firstName": "Cliente",
  "middleName": null,
  "lastName": "Prueba",
  "secondLastName": null,
  "birthDate": "1995-01-01",
  "genderId": 1,
  "addressId": null,
  "email": "cliente{{unique}}@mail.com",
  "password": "Password123*",
  "phoneCountryId": 1,
  "phoneNumber": "300{{unique}}"
}

### AUTH - login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "email": "admin@mail.com",
  "password": "Password123*"
}

### AUTHZ - cliente no debe entrar a endpoints internos: esperado 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

